@node Core
@chapter Core Module

The core module loads @code{libcairo} via Guile's FFI and provides
version query procedures.

@example
(use-modules (cairog))
@end example

@deffn Variable libcairo
The dynamic library handle returned by @code{(dynamic-link "libcairo")}.
Use it to look up additional Cairo symbols via @code{dynamic-func} when
building higher-level bindings.
@end deffn

@deffn Procedure cairo-version
Returns the Cairo library version as an encoded integer
@math{major * 10000 + minor * 100 + micro}.

@example
(cairo-version)  @result{} 11802   ; meaning 1.18.2
@end example
@end deffn

@deffn Procedure cairo-version-string
Returns a pointer to a C string containing the Cairo version.
Convert it with @code{pointer->string}:

@example
(pointer->string (cairo-version-string))  @result{} "1.18.2"
@end example
@end deffn
